snippet.textDisplay: I think the concept is good. However... pretty much every kickoff resulted in the ball starting around the 30 yard line (where they line up). But in the rare instance the returner can break through a wall of 10 defenders, they're gone for an easy TD. I'm not sure it's going to add the excitement they want, as I believe 95% of plays are going to be starting in that 25-35 yard zone, with the other 5% split between penalties vs the kicker or a rare TD return. But... it's still way better than endless touchbacks and/or fair catches.
snippet.textOriginal: I think the concept is good. However... pretty much every kickoff resulted in the ball starting around the 30 yard line (where they line up).
